diff:1192165828:1192165828:=1,236d0%0a%3c Introdution%0a%3c ===========%0a%3c %0a%3c Welcome to GUILDNAME. This guild recognizes that Astro Empires is a%0a%3c strategic war simulator. Economy is king because it fuels the war%0a%3c machines. As such, this guild takes a more militant approach to its%0a%3c activities. '''Our purpose is to attain the first rank for a guild in all categories.'''%0a%3c %0a%3c We recognize that you may be a veteran player. If not, we still welcome%0a%3c you. Please read our [NEWBIE GUIDE] to build your empire. This Policy%0a%3c Guide explains the guild's rank structure and responsibilities,%0a%3c diplomatic philosophy, and member goals. %0a%3c %0a%3c (:*toc:)%0a%3c %0a%3c Hierarchy%0a%3c ==============%0a%3c %0a%3c The GUILDNAME guild has a different rank structure than most. Typically,%0a%3c guilds base rank off of economy, fleet size, etc. Astro Empire (AE) bases%0a%3c rank off of a formula of economy, fleet and technology. Logically, a set%0a%3c of ranks should derive from the AE levels as it is a superset of most%0a%3c ranks structures. This causes one to wonder why exotic ranks are%0a%3c created.%0a%3c %0a%3c Because this is a military game, we adopt a hierarchy%0a%3c of leadership. Players who are actively involved and able to lead others%0a%3c are able to have a greater impact on the guild as a whole. %0a%3c %0a%3c Rank Structure%0a%3c --------------%0a%3c %0a%3c Our ranks derive from the player's responsibility (discussed below). A%0a%3c player choses to become responsible for peers and becomes a Team Leader.%0a%3c A Team Leader is developed to be a Section Leader when each of his team%0a%3c members are themselves Team Leaders. Essentially, they direct their%0a%3c teams, and he directs them. A Fleet Leader is a Section Leader whose%0a%3c team has become Section Leaders. The table below describes this%0a%3c structure, and shows the insignia indicating a leader. Finally, there%0a%3c are other indicators when a player is on probation or in jeopardy of%0a%3c losing guild status.%0a%3c %0a%3c ||class=structure cellspacing=0%0a%3c ||! Insignia ||! Title ||! Description ||%0a%3c || &#0198; || Commander || Overall responsible for guild management ||%0a%3c || &#8984; || Fleet Leader || Responsible for 4 Sections (80 players) ||%0a%3c || &#0167; || Section Leader || Responsible for 4 Teams (20 players) ||%0a%3c || &#1151; || Team Leader || Responsible for 4 Members ||%0a%3c %0a%3c '''Indicators:'''%0a%3c * &#0222; Probation%0a%3c * &#0215; In danger of being booted %0a%3c %0a%3c Responsibilities%0a%3c ----------------%0a%3c %0a%3c Commander%0a%3c ~~~~~~~~~~~%0a%3c %0a%3c The Commander is an honorary title bestowed regardless of rank. The%0a%3c Commander manages the overall guild activities and chairs the Fleet%0a%3c Counsel.%0a%3c %0a%3c Fleet Leader%0a%3c ~~~~~~~~~~~%0a%3c %0a%3c A Fleet Leader coordinates activities with his team of Section Leaders.%0a%3c Fleet Leaders agree to engage in aggressive wars in Fleet Counsel. Fleet%0a%3c Leaders may negotiate treaties with rival guilds.%0a%3c %0a%3c Section Leader%0a%3c ~~~~~~~~~~~%0a%3c %0a%3c Section Leaders manages activities with his team of Team Leaders. They%0a%3c are authorized to engage in minor wars. They are also guild recruiters.%0a%3c They are responsible for ensuring their Team Leaders are adequately%0a%3c involved in their teams, and for helping their Team Leaders to become%0a%3c Section Leaders. Section Leaders are responsible for enforcing%0a%3c discipline (kicking idle or disciplinary players). Section Leaders may%0a%3c spectate the Fleet Counsel. Because of the size of a Section is 20%0a%3c members, a Section Leader will likely command teams within his Galaxy.%0a%3c During mobilization, he will work with his Team Leaders to identify and%0a%3c prioritize targets within his sphere of influence. During war, he will%0a%3c coordinate activities and shift focus as necessary.%0a%3c %0a%3c Team Leader%0a%3c ~~~~~~~~~~~%0a%3c %0a%3c A Team Leader directs his team members. He is responsible for ensuring%0a%3c that his members have adequate defenses, and helps coordinate support%0a%3c for when one of his team members is attacked. During war, teams work%0a%3c together in attack and defense. When each team member has fully%0a%3c developed defenses and an adequate attack fleet, the members may then%0a%3c begin taking on junior members and become Team Leaders. Team Leaders are%0a%3c responsible for identifying members of their team who are idle or%0a%3c disciplinary problems. During mobilization, the Team Leader designates%0a%3c targets and works with his Section Leader to coordinate activities. At%0a%3c war, the Team Leader will direct team activities and ensure all members%0a%3c profit from the engagement.%0a%3c %0a%3c Team Member%0a%3c ~~~~~~~~~~~%0a%3c %0a%3c A Team Member is responsible for ensuring his bases are adequately%0a%3c defended and that he builds an adequate attack fleet. Adequacy is based%0a%3c on his tenure on Delta. He must continually work to improve his economy.%0a%3c The must report any combat they engage in (attack or defense). At peace,%0a%3c he will help monitor rival bases in his region. At mobilization, he will%0a%3c report on target base locations and fleet sizes.  At war, he will attack%0a%3c rival bases as directed and support team members under attack.%0a%3c %0a%3c Diplomacy%0a%3c =========%0a%3c %0a%3c This guild's diplomacy must always serve its constituency and stated%0a%3c goal. Members will support guild diplomacy.%0a%3c %0a%3c Non-Aggression Pacts%0a%3c --------------------%0a%3c %0a%3c n%0a%3c %0a%3c Alliances%0a%3c ---------%0a%3c %0a%3c n%0a%3c %0a%3c Cease Fires%0a%3c -----------%0a%3c %0a%3c n%0a%3c %0a%3c Scout Taps%0a%3c ----------%0a%3c %0a%3c GUILDNAME encourages scout taps on all rivals and friendlies. Just be%0a%3c prepared to defend yourself. Scout taps against member bases subjects%0a%3c that member to being put on report. We encourage defense build-up by%0a%3c allowing guild members to tap one-another. As a new member is assigned a%0a%3c Team Leader who is responsible for him, taps should never occur.%0a%3c %0a%3c Member Goals%0a%3c ============%0a%3c %0a%3c As a member of our guild, you are expected to help us fulfill the%0a%3c guild's goals. This section discusses goals a member must make to remain%0a%3c in the guild. Overall, the member is obligated to keep his Team Leader%0a%3c fully informed of his base locations and any situation that may impact%0a%3c these goals.%0a%3c %0a%3c Activity%0a%3c --------%0a%3c %0a%3c Members are encouraged to visit Delta at least daily. Please also glance%0a%3c over the forum and check the [CHANGES] page for any changes to policy.%0a%3c Inactivity for more than 3 days without prior notice to your next-level%0a%3c superior risks expulsion.%0a%3c %0a%3c Defensive Fleet Goals%0a%3c ---------------------%0a%3c %0a%3c ||class=structure cellspacing=0%0a%3c ||! Quality ||! Size ||! Extras ||%0a%3c ||'''I'''deal ||500x || 4x Disrupter Turrets, 10 Command Centers, P-Shield ||%0a%3c ||'''S'''uperb ||400x || 2x Disrupter Turrets, 10 Command Centers ||%0a%3c ||'''G'''reat ||300x || 2x Best Turrets, 10 Command Centers ||%0a%3c ||'''A'''dequate ||200x || 2x Best Turrets, 5 Command Centers ||%0a%3c ||'''M'''inimal ||100x || 1x Best Turrets ||%0a%3c %0a%3c There are several levels of defensive fleet quality. The table above%0a%3c helps visualize the quality of fleets. Each month, a player should%0a%3c attain the next level of fleet quality. Thus, a player should reach the%0a%3c Good-quality fleet month by the end of his second month. It may be%0a%3c helpful for the member to use the emboldened letter in his fleet%0a%3c identifier to show its quality at a glance, although Sections are%0a%3c encouraged to adopt their own method as one method may reveal fleet%0a%3c quality to rival guilds. Regardless, a scout taps against your bases are%0a%3c not acceptable and you will be put on report.%0a%3c %0a%3c Ideal%0a%3c ~~~~~~%0a%3c %0a%3c Each base must have at least 500 times more fleet (i.e. 500 fleet%0a%3c multiple) on his base than that base generates in economy. Thus, a base%0a%3c generating 100 economy needs a 500,000 defense fleet. With this fleet,%0a%3c the base must have 10 Command Centers, four Disrupter Turrets, and a%0a%3c Planetary Shield. As a cherry on the top, a Leviathan with 5 Battleships%0a%3c might be nice. This could generate a 4000/200/40/2 FT/CR/HC/BB fleet%0a%3c (624K points). However, economies of 300+ make this ideal goal a%0a%3c continuing challenge.%0a%3c %0a%3c Initial%0a%3c ~~~~~~~%0a%3c %0a%3c Obviously the ideal is difficult to attain. Players do not need to start%0a%3c building fleet until Day 6. By that day, players should immediately%0a%3c build 100 FT to cover their bases as well as one level of their best%0a%3c turrets. The Initial goal must be met by Day 14.%0a%3c %0a%3c Medial%0a%3c ~~~~~~%0a%3c %0a%3c Once the initial defenses are established, the member should seek to%0a%3c build a basic fleet (2000/100/20/1 FT/CR/HC/BB). This is a 312,000-point%0a%3c fleet, which is a 300 fleet multiple on a 100-econ planet. A logical%0a%3c step between initial and medial defenses is to build 1200 FT, then%0a%3c build the 100 CR, then 800 FT (totalling 2000 FT), then 20 HC, then 1%0a%3c BB. Once this fleet is built, the member should expand the fleet by that%0a%3c ratio until the ideal fleet size is attained for that base.%0a%3c %0a%3c Offensive Fleet Goals%0a%3c ---------------------%0a%3c %0a%3c The offensive fleet goal is easier to describe. The ideal fleet goal is%0a%3c a 500 fleet multiple for each base. That is, each base supports two%0a%3c ideal defensive fleets---one is just offensive. Assuming you have ten%0a%3c bases at 100 econ, that is a 5,000,000 point offensive fleet. Your total%0a%3c fleet size is 10,000,000. By comparison, the highest fleet-ranked player%0a%3c on Alpha has a 32.4 million point fleet.%0a%3c %0a%3c Scouting%0a%3c --------%0a%3c %0a%3c Each member should keep track of rival bases within the Region of his%0a%3c base. As one tenant of empire building is not to have more than one base%0a%3c in a Region, this means that a player should be able to monitor at least nine%0a%3c regions. There are 100 regions in a Galaxy. So, 11 players should be%0a%3c able to keep tabs on an entire galaxy. That means that a Section should%0a%3c easily be able to monitor and dominate a Galaxy. Naturally, team members%0a%3c can negotiate monitoring activities.%0a%3c %0a%3c When we mobilize, members will focus their attention on scouting guild%0a%3c bases with whom we will war against. This includes calculating what is%0a%3c necessary to occupy rival bases and optimizing an offensive fleet.%0a%3c %0a%3c (:comment This page has been edited using Pywe:)%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
